---
import SiteLayout from '../layouts/SiteLayout.astro';
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Webleee"
  description="Starter terms of service for Webleee website build, hosting, and monthly management services."
>
  <section class="bg-midnight py-20 text-white">
    <div class="site-shell">
      <p class="text-xs font-black uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-lime">Terms of Service</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 max-w-4xl font-display text-5xl font-black leading-tight sm:text-6xl">Terms of Service.</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-white/72">
        These starter terms outline the kind of service terms Webleee should finalize before public launch.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-white py-20">
    <div class="site-shell max-w-4xl">
      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-line bg-skywash p-5 text-sm font-semibold leading-7 text-navy">
        These starter legal pages should be reviewed before public launch. They are not legal advice.
      </div>

      <div class="mt-10 space-y-10 text-slatebody">
        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-navy">Services</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-8">
            Webleee provides website design, website build, deployment, hosting setup, and monthly website management services for businesses. Exact deliverables should be confirmed in writing before work starts.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-navy">Client responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-8">
            Clients are responsible for providing accurate business details, content, logos, images, domain access, review feedback, and approvals needed to complete the website.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-navy">Payment and cancellation</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-8">
            Payment amounts, billing dates, cancellation notice, unpaid work, and restart fees are placeholders and must be finalized before Webleee publishes fixed service terms.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-navy">Ownership and migration</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-8">
            Ownership, source files, hosting access, domain access, and migration terms should be agreed before launch so both Webleee and the client understand what happens if services end.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-black text-navy">Monthly management and support scope</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 leading-8">
            Monthly management may include hosting, updates, technical checks, minor content changes, and support. Exact limits, response times, excluded work, and priority support terms should be documented per plan.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
